pages.title: Humpback Whale
pages.text: The humpback whale ($(o)Megaptera novaeangliae$()) is a species of baleen whale.$(br2)It is a rorqual; a member of the family Balaenopteridae.$(br2)Adults range in length from 14–17 m ($(o)46–56 ft$()) and weigh up to 40 metric tons ($(o)44 short tons).
